        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2019-05-28 02:54:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nIs it necessary to land this patch via the multi-rail branch?  There are already a huge number of unrelated patches on this branch, which makes it expensive to rebase, and IMHO unnecessarily delays landing unrelated fix patches that could be landed sooner. \n\nOne option would be to submit a merge patch at the end of the fixes (maybe LU-11551) and then if that passes testing and is landed there will be fewer patches on this branch. That can be done without affecting the rest of this branch, just checkout the LU-11551 patch, and submit a merge patch. It will be tested separately and can then land.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
